					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Kunio wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">how to set a variable to random in nbasic?</div>
<br />The NES doesn't have any built-in means of generating random numbers. If the author of nbasic didn't create a function for this (isn't there a documentation about the language?), you have to make one yourself. Search google for "6502 PRNG" (PRNG stands for pseudo random number generator) and you should get a few usable routines.
<br />
<br />Sorry if most of us can't help with nbasic stuff, but nobody really uses it for anything serious. Many games made with nbasic by its creator don't work on the real console (we're not sure if nbasic itself has any part in this), so it isn't considered a valid tool by serious developers.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

