					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Horv wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">:?  i'm not sure of it. How can I set the attributes?</div>
<br />
<br />For the sprites?  Remember that the sprite and background palettes are separate (so a full palette file is generally 32 bytes, each section being 16).
<br />
<br />Then to select the palette for the sprite, you know the sprites are defined by 4 bytes (in some call it OAM - object attribute memory).  So if you sprite DMA from $0200 (you should - don't use the $2004 register), you have this pattern in RAM:
<br />byte 0: Y position
<br />byte 1: tile #
<br />byte 2: attribute
<br />byte 3: X position
<br />.. same thing for the following 63 sprites..
<br />
<br />Look up the exact meaning of byte 2, and you'll see.  It allows X/Y flipping, palette selection, and background priority to be set.  I'm just going by memory, but I'm pretty sure you can write $00 - $03 to it to select just the palette attribute and it will leave the other settings at the 'default'.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

