			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Horv wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The error code is: Overflow error! <br /><br />What's the problem? <img src="./images/smilies/icon_confused.gif" alt=":?" title="Confused" /></div>
<br />
<br />The posted code in incomplete.  I don't know how Y_Pos and X_Pos are defined, that error means it's larger than a byte.  It look like you are putting it in ROM though, so every one of those X and Y positions will be the same (you definitely want to add 8 to the Y position for your 2nd sprite (like in the previous table posted).
<br />
<br />If you want a full animation system that you're free to use, you could look at the one I wrote and use.  <a href="http://www.parodius.com/~memblers/nes/animate.asm" class="postlink">http://www.parodius.com/~memblers/nes/animate.asm</a>  It's flexible (allowing reuse of frames and any delays you want, as well as looping) but is a little complicated as a result.</div>

