						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Kunio wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The definition:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; .inesprg&nbsp; 1<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; .ineschr&nbsp; 1<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; .inesmir&nbsp; 1<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; .inesmap&nbsp; 0<br />&nbsp;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; .org $8000<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; .bank 0<br /><br />Y_Pos&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 20<br /><br />Start:<br />....</div><br /><br />This is the solution to define a variable or isn't it?<br /></div>
<br />
<br />Nope, you need to do that in RAM ($0000-$07FF).  Then your program needs to write 20 to it manually.
<br />
<br />What was happening in that case was that Y_Pos was defined as $8000 (it's a label, so it's an address/pointer).</div>

